155	#UserSearchRecommenders	default	You can suggest members of PCI Evol Biol for considering your recommendation request. A member willing to consider your request becomes the “recommender” of this preprint. The recommender will send your request and your preprint for review. The “recommender” sends the reviews (which may or may not be written anonymously, at the reviewer’s discretion) to the authors and asks for modifications, if required. He/she eventually writes a short text of recommendation (together with the other reviewers, if they are willing to do so) explaining the recommendation, when all the requested modifications have been made.
156	#RecommenderDirectSubmission	default	In this page, you may start a new recommendation process for Peer Community in Evolutionary Biology (PCI Evol Biol) for a postprint article (already published or in press, already reviewed) that draw your attention. Fill in the form with the details of the manuscript to initiate the recommendation process. You will have to find a co-recommender, i.e. a colleague (who may be a member of PCI Evol Biol or not. In such case, your colleague will first have to register as a new member of PCI Evol Biol) who will write with you the recommendation text and sign it. Before starting the recommendation process for the manuscript of your choice, you have to be sure that this is in line with the code of ethical conduct of PCI Evol Biol (that can be found here)
161	#UserAddSuggestedRecommender	default	You can suggest members of PCI Evol Biol for considering your recommendation request. A member willing to consider your request becomes the “recommender” of your preprint and will evaluate it for a possible recommendation.
