347	#RecommenderEditDecisionText	default	For a first round of review, you must obtain at least two reviews of high quality. \r\n\r\n* __Recommend the preprint__ only if the preprint can now serve as reference in the scientific literature.  \r\n* __Ask for a revision__ if you think the process can eventually lead to a recommendation but the preprint needs improvements to attain this point.   \r\n* __Reject this preprint__ if you think that no amelioration can lead to a recommendation.   \r\n \r\n__In case you recommend the preprint__: \r\nYou have to write a so-called **Recommendation text** that will have a DOI and will be published. It should have a nice title, contain between about 300 to 1500 words, describe the context and explain why the preprint is worth a recommendation. Limits of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (at least that of the preprint).
