162	#TemplateEmailForReviewInfo	default	If you want to suggest as a reviewer a person who is not member of Peer Community in Evolutionary Biology, you can use this template e-mail to send him/her a message.\r\n\r\n..................................\r\n\r\nDear XXX\r\n\r\nI’m writing you in my capacity as a recommender for the Peer Community in Evolutionary Biology (PCI Evol Biol). I’m handling a paper preprint by XXX and entitled XXX (doi XXX).  \r\n\r\nI’m wondering if you would be willing to provide a review – possibly within 20 days – of the manuscript. If you are willing, please create an account on the website of PCI Evol Biol (https://evolbiol.peercommunityin.org/). I can then send you a request for review through the website that will have to accept.  \r\n\r\nYou may not yet know about PCI Evol Biol. Briefly, it is a community of researchers in Evolutionary Biology dedicated to reviewing and (if they are high quality) recommending articles publicly available in preprint servers (such as bioRxiv). Our motivation is to establishment a high-profile, free, public evaluation system for identifying high-quality articles. More information can be found on the web site, complete with a short video (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jMhVl__gupg). Review itself works largely like it does for a journal (including the ability to remain anonymous or not, as you like).  \r\n\r\nLet me know if you think you can do the above review.  \r\nThanks in advance  \r\nBest wishes  \r\nXXX  \r\n\r\n..................................
