217	#AcceptPreprintInfoText	default	<font style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2em;font-family:optima">\r\n####<div style="text-align:left">You are about to start the evaluation process of a preprint, i.e. an article neither peer-reviewed nor published or under consideration in a scientific journal. Before starting this process:</div>  \r\n* <div style="text-align:left">You must consider that the preprint has some of the following qualities: crucial, original or previously untested hypotheses, scientific rigor, refinement of the demonstration, outstanding quality of the data and methodology, noteworthy scientific consequences, etc.   \r\n* <div style="text-align:left">You will handle this preprint like an editor in a traditional journal.</div>   \r\n* <div style="text-align:left">You will have to invite reviewers - through the website - and obtain at least two reviews for the first round of reviews.   \r\n* <div style="text-align:left">Reviewers must send their reviews within three weeks and we expect your decision, based on their reviews, within 10 more days.</div>    \r\n* <div style="text-align:left">Several rounds of reviews are often necessary before a preprint is rejected or recommended.</div>     \r\n* <div style="text-align:left">At last, if you decide to recommend this preprint, you will have to write a recommendation text to indicate why you recommend it. This 1/2 to 2 pages text will receive a DOI and could be cited (see [an example of recommendation text](https://evolbiol.peercommunityin.org/public/rec?id=43)).</div>   \r\n********** \r\n####<div style="text-align:left">Details about the evaluation & recommendation process can be found [here](../about/help_generic).</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</font>
